<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
</head>

<body>
    <h1>About CyberSafe</h1>

    <nav>
        <a href="/home">Home</a>
        <a href="/about">About</a>
    </nav>

    <!-- paragrahp section to provide information in the About page -->
    <p>
        CyberSafe is a small Express application created to practice
        routes, EJS views, middleware, static files, forms, and downloads.
    </p>

    <p>
        The topic of this app is cybersecurity because learning how to build
        secure web applications starts with understanding basic security habits.
    </p>

    <!-- Form section to create send Post request -->
    <h2>Security Question Form</h2>

<form action="/submit" method="POST">
    <label for="name">Name:</label>
    <input id="name" name="name" type="text">

    <br><br>

    <label for="concern">Cybersecurity Concern:</label>
    <input id="concern" name="concern" type="text">

    <br><br>

    <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>

</body>
</html>